    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting this \"Connection Reset by Peer\" error on my ec2 instances in us-east-1. it only happens intermittently and usually during peak traffic. i checked the security groups and everything looks theoretically fine but the logs are driving me crazy. \n\nhere is a snippet from cloudwatch:\n2023-10-27T14:22:01Z iid: 4922-X | status: 502 | error: connection reset by peer | client_ip: 192.168.1.45\n\nany idea what might be causing this? specifically looking at network config or security groups.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A \"Connection Reset by Peer\" error, especially during peak traffic, often points to the server or an intermediary device actively closing the connection before it completes. While security groups are usually fine, you should investigate if your load balancer or application instances are hitting resource limits like max connections or memory exhaustion under heavy load. This intermittent nature suggests a temporary resource bottleneck rather than a permanent misconfiguration in the network rules.",
      "source": "target",
